    "summary": "High-pressure conditions developed inside EVAL Reactor 2 during startup following maintenance shutdown, activating the emergency pressure-relief system and discharging 2,347 pounds of flammable ethylene vapor through horizontally aimed piping into ambient air where contractors were working. Welding work likely ignited the vapor cloud, causing fire that injured 23 workers.",
